bludge
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to live off the generosity of others, to sponge;often with on; to cadge, scrounge; sponge (on).
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: From <i>N.Z. English to U.S. English Dictionary</i> at http://nz.com/NZ/Culture/NZDic.html
